cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the application of deep learning techniques for the segmentation of retinal layers from OCT images. This involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNN) and long short-term memory (LSTM) networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep learning techniques for automation, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves the use of medical imaging, which suggests that it could belong to cs.MM (Multimedia) as well. Finally, the paper involves the use of neural networks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
